    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Hire an existing employee through recruiting</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Sometimes open positions can be filled by candidates who are already employees in your organization.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Hire an existing employee through recruiting</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Sometimes open positions can be filled by candidates who are already employees in your organization.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This procedure walks through the steps of hiring an existing employee through the recruiting process.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this procedure, a recruitment project has already been set up, and an existing employee has already submitted an application for the recruitment project.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The demo data company used to create this procedure is USMF.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Human resources &gt; Recruitment &gt; Applications &gt; Applications.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, find application for the employee that you would like to hire.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example:  00002  John Emory</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Application status.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The application status indicates where an application is at in the recruitment process.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Each of these steps is optional.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Typically, an application would move the statuses in the following order:  received, confirmed, and interviewed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>After the interview process, a hiring decision would be made.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Change position.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select the position that you are hiring the employee into.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the New Assignment Start Date field, enter the date that the employee will begin working in the new position.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Assignment end date, enter the date that the employee will stop working in their current position.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The starting date for the new position and the ending date of the old position may overlap.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This can happen when a person is performing duties for both positions during a transition period.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Optionally, you can select a reason code.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Example: Reorganization</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Change position.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You may also change compensation at this time.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If you do not assign compensation at this time, you can change it by going to the worker form, selecting the Compensation tab, and choosing 'Fixed Plan'.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>After you select 'Change position', the status on the application will be updated to 'Employed'.</source>
        </trans-unit>
